<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1193,1470]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1265,1290]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks</emphasis>
: The description illustrates two specimens (PEM R7625 and R7632). No date was provided in the original publication, but the label reads ‘ 
<date box="[620,788,1302,1326]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1930-06-23">23 June 1930</date>
’. All specimens are in good overall condition, but PEM R7625 has a detached tail. 
<bibRefCitation author="Loveridge, A." box="[462,660,1337,1362]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 469" refId="ref21912" refString="Loveridge, A. (1947) Revision of the African lizards of the Family Gekkonidae. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 98, 1 - 469." type="journal article" year="1947">Loveridge (1947)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitt" authorityYear="1927" box="[751,875,1337,1362]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Pachydactylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oculatus">
<emphasis box="[751,875,1337,1362]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. oculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[933,1175,1337,1362]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. m. albomarginatus</emphasis>
in the synonymy of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1845" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Pachydactylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculatus">P. maculatus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
although 
<bibRefCitation author="De Waal, S. W. P." box="[385,562,1373,1398]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref20512" refString="De Waal, S. W. P. (1978) The Squamata (Reptilia) of the Orange Free State, South Africa. Memoirsvan die Nasionale Museum, Bloemfontein, 11, 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1978">De Waal (1978)</bibRefCitation>
regarded 
<emphasis box="[674,912,1373,1398]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. m. albomarginatus</emphasis>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitt" authorityYear="1927" box="[1108,1229,1373,1398]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Pachydactylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oculatus">
<emphasis box="[1108,1229,1373,1398]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. oculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He also reported, in error (p. 22, 24) that the 
<typeStatus box="[482,541,1410,1434]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">types</typeStatus>
in the AMG were missing. Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1110,1169,1410,1434]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">types</typeStatus>
confirms that they are morphologically similar to 
<emphasis box="[456,586,1445,1470]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitt" authorityYear="1927" box="[456,583,1445,1470]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Pachydactylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oculatus">P. oculatus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
